The paper deals with the detection of hidden random fields using sensor networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of autoregressive models and correlation factors suggests a connection to machine learning and data analysis (cs.MA). The examination of energy efficiency in sensor network deployment models is relevant to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), while the use of large deviations principles is a statistical inference technique that falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
